  "prompt": "Are there laws that prevent the disguise of illicit funds?",
  "response": "Yes, many countries have anti-money laundering (AML) laws designed to prevent the disguising of illicit funds. These laws typically require financial institutions to:\n\n1. Perform customer due diligence\n2. Report suspicious transactions\n3. Maintain transaction records\n4. Verify the source of large funds\n5. Implement compliance programs to detect potential money laundering\n\nThe specific regulations vary by country, but international bodies like the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) help establish global standards.",
